::: {#hero-heading}

Research areas include Vision-and-Language Navigation (VLN), Vision-Language Action (VLA), World Action Model (WAM), and AI Agent.


- 2026-Present: Master of Science, Nanyang Technological University, specializing in Machine Learning, under supervision of Prof. [Lihua Xie](https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=Fmrv3J8AAAAJ&hl=en).

- 2021-2025: Bachelor of Engineering (Honours), Chongqing University of Technology, majoring in Computer Science and Technology, under supervision of Prof. [Xiaofei Zhu](https://www.atailab.cn/).

## Internship Experience

::: {.project-header}
[Lenovo (Shanghai) Information Technology Co., Ltd. (LR Robotics Algorithm) — Embodied AI Research Intern (Robotics)]{.project-title}
[2026.05-2026.08]{.project-date}
:::
::: {.project-desc}
Leveraging the Lenovo Morningstar robot as the platform, a collaborative intelligent agent system has been constructed, comprising the task-planning "mastermind" NavAgent and the dual-system navigator InternVLA-N1-DualVLN. NavAgent utilizes the LangGraph state machine and MCP to orchestrate the ROS2 toolkit, handling global 
task parsing, memory storage, telemetry self-checks, and anomaly diagnosis. DualVLN manages specific motion generation: System 2 (2 Hz; fine-tuned QwenVL-2.5) predicts 2D pixel sub-goals, while System 1 (30 Hz; NextDiT) outputs high-frequency physical trajectories. SR increased by 10.1%, SPL increased by 6.7%, NE decreased by 17.6%, and StR decreased by 32.5%.
:::

## Project Experience
::: {.project-header}
[Fine-tuning and Closed-loop Evaluation of SmolVLA Robot Fruit-Grasping Strategies Based on Multimodal Synthetic Data]{.project-title}
[2026.07-2026.08]{.project-date}
:::
::: {.project-desc}
This project establishes an end-to-end development pipeline—comprising multi-object simulated synthetic data generation, VLA policy fine-tuning, and closed-loop evaluation—on AMD GPUs (ROCm). It utilizes the Genesis IK expert controller to capture grasping trajectories of a Franka robotic arm for fruits of various geometries, aggregating and packaging the data into a LeRobot-standard multimodal dataset. Based on this, SmolVLA is fine-tuned, and closed-loop placement validation is conducted in scenarios featuring multiple objects and random perturbations.
:::

::: {.project-header}
[OmniVLN: Open-Set Instance-Level 3D Semantic Mapping with Rotating LiDAR and Panoramic Vision](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.17351){.project-title}
[Co-first Author, IEEE RA-L (SCI Q2 TOP, Under Review)]{.project-date}
:::
::: {.project-desc}
To address the issues of missing spatial reasoning and context explosion in large-scale 3D scenes using LLM, an omnidirectional perception-driven embodied intelligence agent framework was developed based on Python, PyTorch, and ROS2. By constructing a dynamic scene graph as the agent's world model and combining it with a multi-resolution spatial attention mechanism, complex long-range navigation in zero-shot environments was achieved with a success rate of 93.18%, while reducing token costs by up to 69.98%.
:::

::: {.project-header}
[A Review of Data Fusion and Deep Learning Models for Multimodal Sentiment Analysis.](https://www.scitepress.org/Papers/2024/131897/131897.pdf){.project-title}
[First Author, Published to In Proceedings of E-commerce and Artificial Intelligence (ECAI 2024)]{.project-date}
:::


## Honors & Awards
- Outstanding graduates of Chongqing, 2025
- Outstanding Bachelor's Thesis Award, 2025
- National Scholarship, 2024
- Second Prize in the National Undergraduate Data Statistics and Analysis Competition, 2023
- Finalist Award in the CCF National Algorithm Elite Competition, 2023
- Third Prize in the National Finals of the Team Programming Ladder Competition, 2023

:::

